### grid-row-start & grid-row-end

CSS syntax:

- grid-row-start: auto|row-line;<br>
- grid-row-end: auto|row-line|span n;

#### Example

```css
grid-row-start: 2;
grid-row-end: span 2;

#container {
  display: grid;
  justify-items: center;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  grid-gap: 10px;
}

.item {
  grid-area: nav;
}
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas:
    'nav nav . .'
    'nav nav . .';
}

#grid-container {
  display: grid;
  justify-items: start;
}

.grid-items {
  justify-self: end;
}

#container {
  display: grid;
  align-items: start;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  grid-gap: 10px;
}

body {
  counter-reset: section;
}

h3::before {
  counter-increment: section;
  content: 'Section.' counter(section);
}

ol {
  counter-reset: section;
  list-marker-type: none;
}

li::before {
  counter-increment: section;
  content: counters(section, '.') ' ';
}

